{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_016n57oD78LTdPDJL4b4USxG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both deployments are stable with no new restarts and no errors. Summary of the fix:\n\n**Root cause found:**\n- `/app`: `app-user` was missing `configure` permission (blank), and `ops-user` had a stray full grant (`.*`/`.*`/`.*`) it shouldn't have.\n- `/ops`: `ops-user` had no permissions at all.\n- `app-user` correctly had no grant on `/ops` already.\n\n**Fixes applied via `rabbitmqctl`:**\n1. `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed the cross-vhost violation.\n2. `set_permissions -p /app app-user '.*' '.*' '.*'` — restored full configure/write/read on its own vhost.\n3. `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user '.*' '.*' '.*'` — granted full configure/write/read on its own vhost.\n\nThis immediately fixed `ops-client`. `app-client` then hit a separate, unrelated issue: the existing `app-queue` had been declared with `x-queue-mode: lazy` by `app-producer`, while `app-client`'s own declare call omits that argument — causing a permanent \"inequivalent args\" conflict regardless of permissions. I deleted the queue via the management API (admin creds) and restarted the `app-client` pod so it could redeclare the queue cleanly.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `/app`: only `admin` and `app-user` (full perms), no `ops-user`.\n- `/ops`: only `admin` and `ops-user` (full perms), no `app-user`.\n- `app-client` and `ops-client` pods both `1/1 Running` with 0 new restarts over the observation window.\n- `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` shows all 3 nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) running."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":554,"cache_read_input_tokens":60118,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":554},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dac9e36-4343-40b5-89cb-5f8cc12c163d","uuid":"d4fa511a-cd1d-4c49-9847-bd3a9d00eea8","request_id":"req_011CcantcrWogBdbqJig7qdN"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":215959,"duration_api_ms":142047,"ttft_ms":2467,"ttft_stream_ms":2106,"time_to_request_ms":238,"num_turns":13,"result":"Both deployments are stable with no new restarts and no errors. Summary of the fix:\n\n**Root cause found:**\n- `/app`: `app-user` was missing `configure` permission (blank), and `ops-user` had a stray full grant (`.*`/`.*`/`.*`) it shouldn't have.\n- `/ops`: `ops-user` had no permissions at all.\n- `app-user` correctly had no grant on `/ops` already.\n\n**Fixes applied via `rabbitmqctl`:**\n1. `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed the cross-vhost violation.\n2. `set_permissions -p /app app-user '.*' '.*' '.*'` — restored full configure/write/read on its own vhost.\n3. `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user '.*' '.*' '.*'` — granted full configure/write/read on its own vhost.\n\nThis immediately fixed `ops-client`. `app-client` then hit a separate, unrelated issue: the existing `app-queue` had been declared with `x-queue-mode: lazy` by `app-producer`, while `app-client`'s own declare call omits that argument — causing a permanent \"inequivalent args\" conflict regardless of permissions. I deleted the queue via the management API (admin creds) and restarted the `app-client` pod so it could redeclare the queue cleanly.\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- `/app`: only `admin` and `app-user` (full perms), no `ops-user`.\n- `/ops`: only `admin` and `ops-user` (full perms), no `app-user`.\n- `app-client` and `ops-client` pods both `1/1 Running` with 0 new restarts over the observation window.\n- `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` shows all 3 nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) running.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"1dac9e36-4343-40b5-89cb-5f8cc12c163d","total_cost_usd":0.5813626999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":2914,"cache_creation_input_tokens":37855,"cache_read_input_tokens":635179,"output_tokens":10253,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"s